<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="187" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="187">
The new species is mostly similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. henryi" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" rank="species" species="henryi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">B. henryi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1095-8339.1887.tb00532.x" author="Hemsley, WB" editor="Forbes, FB" journalOrPublisher="The Journal of the Linnean Society, Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" pagination="321 - 323" refId="B9" refString="Hemsley, WB, 1887. Begoniaceae. In: Forbes, FB, Hemsley, WB, Eds., An enumeration of all the plants known from China proper, Formosa, Hainan, Corea, the Luchu Archipelago, and the island of Hongkong, together with their distribution and synonymy. The Journal of the Linnean Society, Botany 23: 321 - 323, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1095-8339.1887.tb00532.x" title="Begoniaceae." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1095-8339.1887.tb00532.x" volume="23" volumeTitle="An enumeration of all the plants known from China proper, Formosa, Hainan, Corea, the Luchu Archipelago, and the island of Hongkong, together with their distribution and synonymy." year="1887">Hemsley (1887</bibRefCitation>
: 322), but differs by its glabrous leaves, petiole with linear red dots and pubescent, slightly denticulate leaf margin and fewer stamens.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="187" type="materials_examined">
